# README: tested Unica version

## Requirement

`README.md` must always document the Unica version for which cunica development and successful tests were completed.

## Where in README

Keep a **«Совместимость с Unica»** section near the top of `README.md` (after the project summary, before installation instructions).

The section must include:

- tested Unica version as a link to the GitHub release tag (e.g. `0.6.1` → `v0.6.1`)
- reference to `unica-contract.json` → `developmentVersion` as the source of truth for the target layout

## When to update

Update the README version whenever any of these happen:

1. `developmentVersion` in `unica-contract.json` changes
2. cunica is successfully tested against a new Unica release (install, verify, init, or project E2E)
3. you retarget development to a different Unica release

Do not change the README version speculatively before tests pass.

## Workflow after retargeting Unica

1. Update `unica-contract.json` (`developmentVersion`, `developmentReleaseTag`, required paths/skills if layout changed)
2. Run checks:
   - `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\test-powershell-quality.ps1`
   - `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\install-cunica.ps1 -Verify` (with matching Unica installed)
3. Update **«Совместимость с Unica»** in `README.md` to the new tested version
4. Update related memory-bank notes if the architecture or contract changed

## Consistency

- README tested version must match `unica-contract.json` → `developmentVersion` unless README explicitly notes a temporary mismatch (avoid unless necessary).
- Use normalized version without `v` prefix in text; link to GitHub tag with `v` prefix.
